30 /**
31 * See ISO 18004:2006 Annex D.
32 * Element i represents the raw version bits that specify version i + 7
33 */

37 0x1145D, 0x12A17, 0x13532, 0x149A6, 0x15683,
38 0x168C9, 0x177EC, 0x18EC4, 0x191E1, 0x1AFAB,
39 0x1B08E, 0x1CC1A, 0x1D33F, 0x1ED75, 0x1F250,
40 0x209D5, 0x216F0, 0x228BA, 0x2379F, 0x24B0B,

298Version::Version(int versionNumber, std::initializer_list<int> alignmentPatternCenters, const std::array<ECBlocks, 4> &ecBlocks) :
299 _versionNumber(versionNumber),
300 _alignmentPatternCenters(alignmentPatternCenters),
301 _ecBlocks(ecBlocks)
302{
303 _totalCodewords = ecBlocks[0].totalDataCodewords();
304}
305
306const Version *
307Version::VersionForNumber(int versionNumber)
308{
309 if (versionNumber < 1 || versionNumber > 40) {
310 //throw std::invalid_argument("Version should be in range [1-40].");
311 return nullptr;
312 }
313 return &AllVersions()[versionNumber - 1];
314}
315
316const Version *
317Version::ProvisionalVersionForDimension(int dimension)
318{
319 if (dimension % 4 != 1) {
320 //throw std::invalid_argument("Unexpected dimension");
321 return nullptr;
322 }
323 return VersionForNumber((dimension - 17) / 4);
324}
325
326
327const Version *
328Version::DecodeVersionInformation(int versionBits)
329{
330 int bestDifference = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
331 int bestVersion = 0;
332 int i = 0;
333 for (int targetVersion : VERSION_DECODE_INFO) {
334 // Do the version info bits match exactly? done.
335 if (targetVersion == versionBits) {
336 return VersionForNumber(i + 7);
337 }
338 // Otherwise see if this is the closest to a real version info bit string
339 // we have seen so far
340 int bitsDifference = BitHacks::CountBitsSet(versionBits ^ targetVersion);
341 if (bitsDifference < bestDifference) {
342 bestVersion = i + 7;
343 bestDifference = bitsDifference;
344 }
345 ++i;
346 }
347 // We can tolerate up to 3 bits of error since no two version info codewords will
348 // differ in less than 8 bits.
349 if (bestDifference <= 3) {
350 return VersionForNumber(bestVersion);
351 }
352 // If we didn't find a close enough match, fail
353 return nullptr;
354}

356/**
357* See ISO 18004:2006 Annex E
358*/
359void
360Version::buildFunctionPattern(BitMatrix& bitMatrix) const
361{
362 int dimension = dimensionForVersion();
363 bitMatrix = BitMatrix(dimension, dimension);
364
365 // Top left finder pattern + separator + format
366 bitMatrix.setRegion(0, 0, 9, 9);
367 // Top right finder pattern + separator + format
368 bitMatrix.setRegion(dimension - 8, 0, 8, 9);
369 // Bottom left finder pattern + separator + format
370 bitMatrix.setRegion(0, dimension - 8, 9, 8);
371
372 // Alignment patterns
373 size_t max = _alignmentPatternCenters.size();
374 for (size_t x = 0; x < max; ++x) {
375 int i = _alignmentPatternCenters[x] - 2;
376 for (size_t y = 0; y < max; ++y) {
377 if ((x == 0 && (y == 0 || y == max - 1)) || (x == max - 1 && y == 0)) {
378 // No alignment patterns near the three finder paterns
379 continue;
380 }
381 bitMatrix.setRegion(_alignmentPatternCenters[y] - 2, i, 5, 5);
382 }
383 }
384
385 // Vertical timing pattern
386 bitMatrix.setRegion(6, 9, 1, dimension - 17);
387 // Horizontal timing pattern
388 bitMatrix.setRegion(9, 6, dimension - 17, 1);
389
390 if (_versionNumber > 6) {
391 // Version info, top right
392 bitMatrix.setRegion(dimension - 11, 0, 3, 6);
393 // Version info, bottom left
394 bitMatrix.setRegion(0, dimension - 11, 6, 3);
395 }
396}
